public int[] sort(int[] array) {
    for(int i = 0; i < array.length / 2; i++) {
        int temp = array[i];
        array[i] = array[array.length - i - 1];
        array[array.length - i - 1] = temp;
    }
    return array;
}

I have written a program to find the longest common substring in a set of strings.

import sys

def longest_common_substring(strings):
    if not strings:
        return ""

    # Create a matrix to store the longest common substring for each pair of strings
    matrix = [[0] * len(strings) for _ in range(len(strings))]

    # Fill the matrix with the length of the common substring between each pair of strings
    for i in range(len(strings)):
        for j in range(i + 1, len(strings)):
            if strings[i] == strings[j]:
                matrix[i][j] = 1
            else:
                matrix[i][j] = 0

    # Find the longest common substring by traversing the matrix
    longest_substring = ""
    for i in range(len(strings)):
        for j in range(i + 1, len(strings)):
            if matrix[i][j] > len(longest_substring):
                longest_substring = strings[i][:len(strings[j])] + strings[j][len(strings[i]):]

    return longest_substring

# Test the function with the given set of strings
print(longest_common_substring(["Easy", "Expert", "Elephant"]))

This program works by creating a matrix where each cell represents the length of the common substring between the two strings at the corresponding row and column. The program then fills the matrix with the length of the common substring between each pair of strings. Finally, the program traverses the matrix to find the longest common substring by comparing the length of each cell to the current longest substring. If a cell has a longer length, the program updates the longest substring to include the new substring. The program returns the longest common substring found.

